      <byline class="print_byline">By Buster Olney</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olney, Buster</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York Yankees pitching coach Mel Stottlemyre, recovering from cancer treatment, attends Game 1 of World Series (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Yankees' pitching coach, Mel Stottlemyre, who is recovering from treatment for bone-marrow cancer, strolled into Yankee Stadium yesterday afternoon, sheepishly waving to fans who screamed his name. Stottlemyre had said last week that he would not go to the park when there were lots of fans around, but his arrival before Game 1 was a little later than he had originally planned.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Yankees' pitching coach, Mel Stottlemyre, who is recovering from treatment for bone-marrow cancer, strolled into Yankee Stadium yesterday afternoon, sheepishly waving to fans who screamed his name. Stottlemyre had said last week that he would not go to the park when there were lots of fans around, but his arrival before Game 1 was a little later than he had originally planned.</p>
        <p>''I'm being a little bit sneaky,'' joked Stottlemyre, who said that he would not be anywhere near the field during games.</p>
        <p>Buster Olney</p>
        <p>BASEBALL: SUBWAY SERIES -- WORLD SERIES NOTEBOOK</p>
